The '''Doctor of Literature and Philosophy''', or ''DLitt et Phil'', is a doctoral advanced research degree offered by a number of leading universities in [[South Africa]], such as UJ, the [[University of Johannesburg]]; and UNISA, the [[University of South Africa]]. The degree is equivalent to a [[Doctor of Philosophy|PhD]] and is generally offered in arts, human science ([[humanities]]), and [[social science]] subjects.
==Requirements== At universities such as the University of Johannesburg and the University of South Africa, the degree of Doctor of Literature and Philosophy is assessed by a [[thesis]] examined by a minimum of one internal and two external examiners, with the thesis falling between 60,000 and 90,000 words in length.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unisa.ac.za/contents/colleges/col_grad_studies/docs/Procedures_studies_masters_doctoral_degrees_15June2011.pdf|title=Procedures for Studies for Master's and Doctoral Degrees|date=2008}}</ref> The work must make an original contribution to academic knowledge. A [[Master's degree]] in a relevant subject with average marks of a minimum of 60% is required for admission.<ref>{{url|http://www.unisa.ac.za/qualificationsMD/}}</ref>
The UNISA also offers a Doctor of Literature and Philosophy in Health Studies<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.unisa.ac.za/qualificationsreg/MD/index.asp?link=http://www.unisa.ac.za/qualificationsreg/MD/Qualifications/98422.html | title=Doctor of Literature and Philosophy in Health Studies | publisher=University of South Africa | accessdate=30 July 2016}}</ref> and in [[Environmental Science]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.university-directory.eu/jredirect/135283/Environmental+Engineering/program-courses/Doctorate-PhD/63/University+of+South+Africa/ZA/5065/Doctor+of+Literature+and+Philosophy+%28DLitt+et+Phil%29+in+Environmental+Science#courseheader | title=Doctor of Literature and Philosophy in Environmental Science | publisher=University Directory | accessdate=30 July 2016}}</ref>
