==Production== In October 2010, [[Ubisoft]] and [[Aardman Animations|Aardman]] announced a partnership to produce a TV series pilot and several shorts based on Ubisoft's ''[[Raving Rabbids]]'' franchise.<ref>[http://uk.wii.ign.com/articles/112/1125224p1.html Ubisoft & Aardman to Create Pilot for Animated Television Show Based on Raving Rabbids, IGN]</ref> The following year, it was announced that 78 animated episodes would be made by [[Ubisoft Motion Pictures]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Keslassy |first=Elsa |title=Nick licenses 'Raving Rabbids' |url=http://www.variety.com/article/VR1118044007 |accessdate=October 6, 2011 |newspaper=Variety |date=October 6, 2011}}</ref> The series premiered on [[Nickelodeon]] on August 3, 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2013/07/12/rabbids-invasion-debut-date-announced-and-trailer-revealed |title=Rabbids Invasion: Debut Date Announced and Trailer Revealed |publisher=IGN |date=July 12, 2013 |accessdate=July 17, 2013}}</ref> On December 17, 2013, Nickelodeon renewed the show for a second season of 26 half-hour blocks, with three segments per block.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/12/17/rabbids-invasion-renewed-by-nickelodeon-for-second-season/223206/ |title=‘Rabbids Invasion’ Renewed by Nickelodeon for Second Season |publisher=TVbytheNumbers |date=December 17, 2013 |accessdate=June 19, 2015}}</ref> On June 16, 2015, Nickelodeon renewed the show for a third season.<ref>{{cite web |author=Elsa Keslassy |url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/french-toon-studio-teamto-blossoms-at-10-sells-yellowbird-to-universal-1201520552/ |title=French Toon Studio TeamTO Sells ‘YellowBird’ to Universal |publisher=Variety |date= |accessdate=June 19, 2015}}</ref> A fourth season was announced in July 2018.<ref>{{Citation |last=Les Lapins Crétins Invasion |title=Les Lapins Crétins – Teaser Saison 4 |date=July 10, 2018 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2NF-8yuFeoI|access-date=October 17, 2018}}</ref>
==Broadcast== The series has aired on [[Nickelodeon]] in the United States, on [[YTV (TV channel)|YTV]] and [[Nickelodeon (Canada)|Nickelodeon]] in Canada, and on [[France 3]], [[France 4]] and [[Nickelodeon (France)|Nickelodeon]] in France. It premiered on February 3, 2014, in the [[United Kingdom]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/gaming/news/a543957/rabbids-invasion-coming-to-uk-on-nicktoons-in-february.html |title=Rabbids Invasion coming to UK in February |last=Martin |first=Liam |work=digitalspy.com |date=January 14, 2014 |accessdate=February 15, 2014}}</ref> and [[Ireland]] and on January 28, 2014, in [[Australia]] and [[New Zealand]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2013/12/foxtel-summer-highlights-for-kids.html |title=Foxtel: Summer highlights for kids |last=Knox |first=David |date=December 4, 2013 |work=tvtonight.com.au |accessdate=February 15, 2014}}</ref> In China, ''Rabids Invasion'' is the most-watched children's television series, having gathered over a billion views.<ref>http://kidscreen.com/2017/09/22/with-nintendos-help-ubisoft-grows-rabbids-in-asia/</ref>
==Reception== Emily Ashby of [[Common Sense Media]] gave the show two out of five stars, stating: "''Rabbids Invasion'' tones down the violence for the characters' jump from gaming to the TV, but they still have a lot of fun at the expense of each other and of unsuspecting bystanders, and a lot of their antics would be frowned upon in the real world (using chickens' butts as egg shooters in a mock battle, for instance). Ultimately, though, it's rude, crude, and minimally taxing on viewers' sense of comprehension, so for better or worse, it's bound to appeal to the grade-school set."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.commonsensemedia.org/tv-reviews/rabbids-invasion |title=Rabbids Invasion – Television Review |author=Emily Ashby |work=Commonsensemedia.org |accessdate=August 6, 2013}}</ref>
==Video game== At the 2013 [[Electronic Entertainment Expo]], it was announced that ''Rabbids Invasion'' would be adapted into an interactive TV series, titled ''Rabbids Invasion: The Interactive TV Show''.<ref>{{cite press release |title=Ubisoft® Makes Interactive TV A Reality With Creation Of Rabbids® Invasion The Interactive TV Show |url=https://www.ubisoftgroup.com/en-us/press/detail.aspx?cid=tcm:99-101488&ctid=tcm:95-27313-32 |publisher=Ubisoft |accessdate=June 15, 2014 |date=June 10, 2013}}</ref> The game, which would combine existing television episodes with a series of challenges, was released on [[Xbox 360]], [[Xbox One]] and [[PlayStation 4]] in November 2014, requiring a [[Kinect]] or [[PlayStation Camera]], respectively.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://blog.ubi.com/rabbids-invasion-the-interactive-tv-announced/ |title=Rabbids Invasion: The Interactive TV Show coming this year |publisher=[[Ubisoft]] |author=Anne Lewis |date=June 9, 2013 |accessdate=October 10, 2014}}</ref>
