A '''setup''', in [[storytelling]], is the introduction in a [[plot (narrative)|plot]] of an element that will be useful to the story only later, when the [[Payoff (storytelling)|payoff]] comes.

Most of the important elements that are part of the setup are usually introduced during the [[Exposition (narrative)|exposition]], with which it is sometimes confused. But there can be a setup within a specific [[Scene (drama)|scene]] late in the story, with a [[Character (arts)|character]], object or concept appearing only to be used paragraphs or seconds later.

